title: How Pinterest, Lyft, Uber IPOs might affect FAANG stocks
text: Paul Meeks, portfolio manager of the Wireless Fund, joins "Squawk Box" to give his analysis of how FAANG stocks might expand to make room for Pinterest, Lyft and Uber in the event the companies go public.

title: Is “Techlash” a weakness of the Western political system?
text: An in-depth discussion from CNBC’s special Davos Debate: Shifting Sands on whether the West’s idea of individual freedoms inhibits technology.

title: February housing market index beats expectations
text: CNBC's Rick Santelli reports on the strongest housing market index numbers since October of 2018.

title: Lower market volume due to the holiday could lead to volatility: UBS' Art Cashin
text: Art Cashin, director of floor operations with UBS, joins "Squawk Box" before the bell to discuss what he's watching in the markets.

title: Why Greycroft's Alan Patricof wouldn't buy Uber if it went public
text: Alan Patricof, founder and managing director at Greycroft, joins "Squawk Box" to discuss what IPOs he's expecting in 2019.

title: Now is a good time to buy Bitcoin, Blockchain Capital's Bogart says
text: Spencer Bogart, Blockchain Capital partner, discusses the outlook for Bitcoin and cryptocurrencies with Bloomberg Inteligence's Mike McGlone and Emily Chang on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: Payless closing all 2700 stores nationwide, filing for bankruptcy
text: Seana Smith, Melody Hahm and Zach Guzman of Yahoo Finance discuss Payless shoe stores filing for Chapter 11 bankruptcy and closing all 2700 stores nationwide.

title: Here's what needs to change on the 401(k)
text: Jason Zweig, WSJ columnist, joins 'The Exchange' to discuss how America's retirement plan, the 401(k) is outdated and what needs to change.

title: Elder Tech, made for tech-challenged seniors
text: Kai Stinchcombe, True Link Financial CEO, joins 'The Exchange' to discuss how his company is improving the lives of seniors through technology designed specially for the age group.

title: Here's what you need to know about the Huawei debate
text: CNBC's Deirdre Bosa reports on the debate regarding a potential executive order banning usage of Huawei technology and who could get hurt from the order.

title: One Fact The Market Bears Don't Mention
text: Even though the stock market continues to climb it has still not convinced many stock market bears. Many base their conclusions on fundamental analysis so the market's rally has not changed their outlook.

title: What's wrong & what's right with the traditional meat and dairy industry
text: We visited Just headquarters to try out its latest product, Just Egg. Udi Lazimy showed us the vast plant library, Chingyao walks us through their Discovery Platform, and CEO Joshua Tetrick explains what's wrong and what's right with the traditional meat and dairy industry. Produced / Shot / Edited: Gregory S. Manalo

title: Uber pushes back against New York City
text: Uber Technologies Inc.’s revenue growth slowed and losses persisted in the fourth quarter, posing a challenge to investors trying to figure out Uber’s value as it prepares for a public offering this year. Bloomberg's Eric Newcomer has more on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: Dow soars more than 400 points on trade optimism
text: Stocks soar on hopes of a U.S.-China trade deal. Is everything awesome again? With CNBC's Melissa Lee and the Fast Money traders, Tim Seymour, Brian Kelly, Steve Grasso and Guy Adami.

title: Uber FY 2018 Results: Uber's losses narrowed, revenue grew
text: CNBC's Deirdre Bosa reports on new 2018 results for Uber, where losses narrowed compared to 2017, but revenue growth slowed. This is right as the company is expected to go public in 2019.

title: Here are the four best-performing sectors so far in 2019
text: CNBC's Dom Chu looks ahead at the day's market action.
